#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn47.32"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.32:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.32:0.2"
msgid "4. Ananussutavagga "
msgstr "4. Not Learned From Anyone Else "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.32:0.3"
msgid "32. Virāgasutta "
msgstr "32. Fading Away "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn47.32:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four kinds of mindfulness meditation, when developed and cultivated, lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn47.32:2.1"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn47.32:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn47.32:2.3"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … "

msgctxt "sn47.32:2.4"
msgid "citte … pe … "
msgstr "mind … "

msgctxt "sn47.32:2.5"
msgid "dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.32:2.6"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro satipaṭṭhānā bhāvitā bahulīkatā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattantī”ti. "
msgstr "These four kinds of mindfulness meditation, when developed and cultivated, lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.32:2.7"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

